Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at Brushy Creek Baptist Church in Taylors, South Carolina, where he discussed various topics including the economy, national defense, religious freedom, and support for Israel. He highlighted the achievements of the Trump administration, such as tax cuts, job creation, and the defeat of ISIS. Pence also emphasized the administration's commitment to protecting the sanctity of human life and defending religious liberty both at home and abroad. He mentioned the persecution faced by Christians in countries like China and Nicaragua, and expressed solidarity with those suffering for their faith. Pence concluded by urging the audience to pray for America and to continue their important work in their communities.